******************************************************************************

@NODE configuration "Configuration."

  AModPlay  is  configured by it's workbench tooltypes.  The
  tooltypes  supported  by  AModPlay  (and  how to set them)
  are...

    @{" CX_POPUP " LINK cx_popup}
    @{" CX_POPKEY " LINK cx_popkey}
    @{" CX_PRIORITY " LINK cx_priority}
    @{" MODULEDIR " LINK moduledir}
    @{" QUITIFACTIVE " LINK quitifactive}
    @{" XPKQUIET " LINK xpkquiet}
    @{" GUIX " LINK guix}
    @{" GUIY " LINK guiy}
    @{" MENUFONT " LINK menufont}
    @{" GUIFONT " LINK guifont}
    @{" DRAGDROPLOADONLY " LINK dragdroploadonly}

@ENDNODE

@NODE cx_popup "CX_POPUP ToolType."

  @{b}CX_POPUP@{ub}

    If  this  tooltype is set to YES then AModPlay will open
    it's  GUI  when it's launched, otherwise the GUI will be
    hidden.

    The default setting for this tooltype is NO.

@ENDNODE

@NODE cx_popkey "CX_POPKEY ToolType."

  @{b}CX_POPKEY@{ub}

    This  tooltype  is used to set the popup key combination
    that  will open AModPlay's GUI.  for more information on
    how to set this tooltype please refer to the commodities
    section in your workbench manual.

    The default setting for this tooltype is ALT SHIFT A.

@ENDNODE

@NODE cx_priority "CX_PRIORITY ToolType."

  @{b}CX_PRIORITY@{ub}

    For  more information on how to set this tooltype please
    refer  to  the  commodities  section  in  your workbench
    manual.

    The default value for this tooltype is 0.

@ENDNODE

@NODE moduledir "MODULEDIR ToolType."

  @{b}MODULEDIR@{ub}

    This  tooltype  lets  the  user  specify  where  his/her
    modules   are   stored.    AModPlay   will   open   it's
    filerequester in this directory.

    The  default  directory  for  this  tooltype is MODULES:

@ENDNODE

@NODE quitifactive "QUITIFACTIVE ToolType."

  @{b}QUITIFACTIVE@{ub}

    When  AModPlay is launched it will check wether there is
    already  another  AModPlay running.  If so then AModPlay
    exits.   If  this  tooltype if set to YES, AModPlay will
    force the existing AModPlay to quit before exiting.

    The default setting for this tooltype is NO

@ENDNODE

@NODE xpkquiet "XPKQUIET ToolType."

  @{b}XPKQUIET@{ub}

    When  unpacking  an XPK packed file AModPlay will open a
    little  window informing the user that the file is being
    unpacked  (otherwise  it  might  look  like AModPlay has
    crashed).   If this tooltype is set to YES then AModPlay
    will  not  open  this information window, which might be
    helpful if you have an 060 or better where XPK is fairly
    transparent.

    The default setting for this tooltype is NO

    NOTE:
    When using XPK packed files AModPlay will unpack them to
    t:amodplay.tmp.   The  tempfile will be removed when the
    module is unloaded or when AmodPlay exits.

@ENDNODE

@NODE guix "GUIX ToolType."

  @{b}GUIX@{ub}

    This  tooltype  lets  the  user  specify  X  position of
    AModPlay's GUI when it opens.

    The default setting for this tooltype is 24.

@ENDNODE

@NODE guiy "GUIY ToolType."

  @{b}GUIY@{ub}

    This  tooltype  lets  the  user  specify  Y  position of
    AModPlay's GUI when it opens.

    The default setting for this tooltype is 16.

@ENDNODE

@NODE menufont "MENUFONT ToolType."

  @{b}MENUFONT@{ub}

    This tooltype lets the user specify the font used by the
    menustrip when AModPlay's GUI is open.

    The default value for this tooltype is TOPAZ/8.

@ENDNODE

@NODE guifont "GUIFONT ToolType."

  @{b}GUIFONT@{ub}

    This tooltype lets the user specify the font used by the
    gadgets in AModPlay's GUI when it is open.

    The default value for this tooltype is TOPAZ/8.

@ENDNODE

@NODE dragdroploadonly "DRAGDROPLOADONLY ToolType."

  @{b}DRAGDROPLOADONLY@{ub}

    If  this  tooltype is set to YES then any icons that get
    dropped  into AModPlay's GUI window (assuming it is open
    and  the file is a module) will get loaded only and will
    not begin replaying.

    The default setting for this tooltype is NO.

@ENDNODE

******************************************************************************

@NODE arexx "AREXX interface."

  AModPlay   can   be  controlled  totally  via  it's  ARexx
  interface.  It's ARexx portname is "AMODPLAY".

  If  an  error  occurs during any arexx operation, AModPlay
  always returns RC_FATAL (20)

  Here  are  the commands that AModPlay knows and how to use
  them..

    @{" LOAD " LINK cmd_load}
    @{" PLAY " LINK cmd_play}
    @{" STOP " LINK cmd_stop}
    @{" CONT " LINK cmd_cont}
    @{" UNLOAD " LINK cmd_unload}
    @{" SHOW " LINK cmd_show}
    @{" HIDE " LINK cmd_hide}
    @{" ABOUT " LINK cmd_about}
    @{" QUIT " LINK cmd_quit}

@ENDNODE

@NODE cmd_load "CMD_LOAD"

@{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}

 Loads  a  module  for playing.  If no filename is passed to
 it,  AModPlay opens a requester allowing the user to select
 a module to play.

@{b}SYNTAX@{ub}

 load (filename)

@{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}

 /* load_with_no_name.amp. */
 address AMODPLAY load

@{b}EXAMPLE2@{ub}

 /* load_from_arg.amp. */
 parse arg filename
 address AMODPLAY load filename

@ENDNODE

@NODE cmd_play "CMD_PLAY"

@{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}

 Begins playback of the current module.

@{b}SYNTAX@{ub}

 play ()

@{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}

 /* play.amp. */
 address AMODPLAY play

@ENDNODE

@NODE cmd_stop "CMD_STOP"

@{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}

 Stops playback of the current module.

@{b}SYNTAX@{ub}

 stop ()

@{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}

 /* stop.amp. */
 address AMODPLAY stop

@ENDNODE

@NODE cmd_cont "CMD_CONT"

@{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}

 Resumes  playback  of  a module that was previously stopped
 with the stop command.

@{b}SYNTAX@{ub}

 stop ()

@{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}

 /* cont.amp. */
 address AMODPLAY cont

@ENDNODE

@NODE cmd_unload "CMD_UNLOAD"

@{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}

 Stops current module and flushes it from memory.

@{b}SYNTAX@{ub}

 unload ()

@{b} EXAMPLE@{ub}

 /* unload.amp. */
 address AMODPLAY unload

@ENDNODE

@NODE cmd_show "CMD_SHOW"

@{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}

 Opens AModPlay's GUI.

@{b}SYNTAX@{ub}

 show ()

@{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}

 /* show.amp. */
 address AMODPLAY show

@ENDNODE

@NODE cmd_hide "CMD_HIDE"

@{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}

 Closes AmodPlay's GUI.

@{b}SYNTAX@{ub}

 hide ()

@{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}

 /* hide.amp. */
 address AMODPLAY hide

@ENDNODE

@NODE cmd_about "CMD_ABOUT"

@{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}

 Displays information about the currently loaded module.

@{b}SYNTAX@{ub}

 about ()

@{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}

 /* about.amp. */
 address AMODPLAY about

@ENDNODE

@NODE cmd_quit "CMD_QUIT"

@{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}

 Forces AmodPlay to release all system resources and quit.

@{b} SYNTAX@{ub}

 /* quit.amp. */
 quit ()

@{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}

 address AMODPLAY quit

@ENDNODE

