@NODE requirements "Requirements"

 AModPlay needs the following things to work...

  - Any Amiga with V37+ (tested on trusty old A2000).

  - BFBPlayMaster library package (included).

  - ReqTools library v38 or better.

  - RexxMaster up and running.

@ENDNODE

******************************************************************************


@NODE introduction "Introduction"

 Welcome to AModPlay :^)

 AModPlay     is     an     AREXX    interface    for    the
 @{"BFBPlayMaster.library" LINK BFBPlayMasterUsr.readme/main}  (a  multi-format music module player
 library   programmed   by   a   cool   guy   called  Jarkko
 Vatjus-Anttila <quaid@kempele.fi> (incase you didn't follow
 the link)), so what AModPlay does is play music modules.

 I  have several module-player programs that are pretty cool
 but they all look extremly ugly (sorry authors but I really
 hate  topaz.font  based  GUI's) on my Workbench and none of
 them  seem  willing  or  able  to iconify as nothing (eg be
 invisible), thus was born AModPlay.  I really programmed it
 because      of      the      afforementioned     brilliant
 BFBPlayMaster.library  which  is really simple to use (from
 almost any programming language).

 Once  AModPlay is running it waits for  @{"ARexx commands" LINK arexx} to be
 sent  to  it.  In turn it uses these commands to play music
 modules.

 AModPlay  is  also  a  commodity  and  as such has a hotkey
 combination  which  when  pressed activates AModPlay's GUI.
 The  GUI  has two rows of buttons which correspond directly
 with the included ARexx scripts.

 AModPlay's GUI window is also an AppWindow.  This means you
 can  Drag'n'Drop  icons anywhere in it's window area and as
 long  as  it  is  a  valid and recognized module it will be
 loaded and played.

 Enjoy,
       Cliff Earl.

 Sadly it looks like this will be the last AModPlay ever :^(
 as I cannot contact the  author of the BFBPlay libraries to
 find out  if he is planning to update  them. Well it's been
 fun hunting the bugs  and getting some feedback on AModPlay
 from my one repliant :^(


@ENDNODE

