@NODE history "HISTORY IN THE MAKING."

 V1.60 (12.2.1998)

  - Found potential guru maker which was some leftover code used
    for debugging puropses in the last couple of versions. oops.

  - Fixed problems  with gadtools menus that  made the BARLABELS
    the wrong colour.

 V1.59 (27.12.1997)

  - Tidied up source  using new ReqTools  code and incudes (very
    minor update which does not really warrant another release).

 V1.58 (25.8.1997)

  - BUGFIX
    Fixed  Drop'n'Drag  code.   Thanks  to  Robert  Whitaker for
    finding  the  bug  but  it  was not me :^).  The AutoDoc for
    dos.library  failed  to inform me that _LVONameFromLock does
    not  append  a  "/" at the end of the string it generates if
    the path ends with a sub-directory.  Grrrr...

  - Changed  XPK  code.  If XPKMaster library can not  be opened
    then  no  XPK  unpacking  can be performed.  Before AModPlay
    would fail to start.



 V1.57 (24.8.1997)

  - Added HotKey's to gadgets and HotKey code to use em :^)

  - Found  installer  archive (with docs) on an  old source disk
    and  fixed AModPlay's installer script.  Now it will install
    the BFBPlay library set correctly.



 V1.56 (22.8.1997)

  - Added code to to inform user about startup errors.

  - Added  code to inform user about errors  when AModPlay fails
    to open it's GUI.

  - When using CX hotkey you had to flip back to whatever screen
    AModPlay  happended  opened  it's GUI on.  Now will pop that
    screen to front.

  - AmodPlay will now open it's GUI on the front PubScreen.



 V1.55 (20.8.1997)

  - VERY simple layout engine for GUI.
    The  gui is now sort of font adaptive (some people don't
    like  my  beloved Opal.font).  User can choose the fonts
    AModPlay   uses  in  it's  GUI  state.   The  fonts  are
    specified in the tooltypes below...

  - MENUFONT tooltype.
    Allows user to specify the font used in the GUI's menus.
    If not present then topaz/8 will be used.

  - GUIFONT tooltype.
    Allows  user  to  specify  the  font  used  in the GUI's
    gadgets.  If not present then topaz/8 will be used.



 V1.54 (19.8.1997)

  - Drag'n'Drop.
    AModPlay's GUI window is now an AppWindow.  Now you can
    drag'n'drop a music module anywhere in AModPlay's window
    and  it  will  get  loaded.   If the appwindow cannot be
    created then Drag'n'Drop features are disabled.

  - DRAGDROPLOADONLY tooltype.
    If  YES  then  AModPlay  will only load modules that are
    dropped into it's window.  If NO then the dropped module
    will  get  played as well.  If not present then the "NO"
    syntax applies.

  - BUGFIX
    The  XPK error code was flawed.  It was trying to access
    an  odd  memory  address  and  was  also  addressing  it
    incorrectly (move.l instead of lea).



 V1.53 (18.8.1997)

  - CX support.
    AModPlay is now a commodity.

  - Commodity type tooltypes.
    The standard 3 are supplied...
    - CX_POPUP
    - CX_POPKEY
    - CX_PRIORITY



  V1.52 (17.8.1997)

   - Graphic User Interface.
    A groovy GUI thanks to GadToolsBox & GTAsmGen (My custom
    ASM generator for GTB).

  - SHOW command.
    This command will tell AModPlay to open it's GUI.

  - HIDE command.
    This command will tell AModPlay to close it's GUI.

  - GUIX tooltype
    This  tooltype  can be set to open the GUI window at the
    desired x position.  If not present AModPlay uses 24.

  - GUIY tooltype
    This  tooltype  can be set to open the GUI window at the
    desired y position.  If not present AModPlay uses 16.

  - show.amp and hide.amp.
    ARexx scripts for the above mentioned new commands.

  - UNLOAD command update
    This  command will now flush the XPK tempfile every time
    it's  called  (if  the  file  is  still  alive that is).
    Previously  the  file was only deleted when AModPlay was
    quit.



 NEW FOR V1.51 (16.8.1997)

  - XPK support.
    Simple  XPK  support  implemented via XPKMaster library.
    If  a  packed file is encountered it will be unpacked to
    "t:amodplay.tmp" and played from that file.

  - XPKQUIET tooltype.
    If  YES  then  no  window will open to inform the caller
    what  the  program is doing while XPKMaster is unpacking
    the XPK-packed file.

   - QUITIFACTIVE tooltype.
    If  YES  then AModPlay will not load if another AModPlay
    is resident in memory, and the resident AModPlay will be
    forced  to fail all waiting commands and purge it's self
    from memory.



  V1.4 - Major update. (13.8.1997)

  - Added  the  QUITIFACTIVE  tooltype   so  user  can  tell
    AModPlay  to  quit  when  it  is  run  and finds it'self
    alreadypresent.    Thanks   to   Mikael   Lund  for  the
    suggestion.

  - While  implementing  QUITIFACTIVE I got fed up with  the
    code  and  rewrote most of it.  This will make it easier
    to  implement a full GUI interface later and also showed
    up  the evil BUG in the "continue" code that was causing
    deadend crashes of type $80000004 :^(



  V1.1 - First public release.

  - Several  changes  to  the  documentation.  Especially  I
    forgot  to  mention  that  you  need  RexxMaster running
    before AModPlay will work, oops :^)

  - Added  "Status"  to the About requester (rather  useless
    but I thought I might as well add it while I was working
    on said requester).

  - Added "SampleInfo" function to the About requester.  Now
    Jarrko   can  see  the  sample  infos.   The  format  is
    SampleSize,SampleName.   It's  this  way  to let it look
    nicer  with  a  proportional  font (and I didn't want to
    yukkify  my  nice  Opal/13 WB by adding a topaz textatrr
    tag to the requester).



  V1.0
  - Only released to author of BFBPlayMaster.library.

@ENDNODE

